Mildred S. COHEN, Doing Business as Port Orchard Department Store, Appellant, v. Chester BOWLES, Administrator, Office of Price Administration, Appellee. No. 11153. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 26, 1945. Frederick B. Cohen, of Bremerton, Wash., for appellant. George Moncharsh, Deputy Adm’r for Enforcement, OPA, of Washington, D. C., Herbert H. Bent, Regional Litigation Atty., OPA, of San Francisco, Cal., and George B. Kautz, Atty., OPA, of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in above cause be dismissed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
